1
00:00:07,695 --> 00:00:08,529
Hello, Mom?

2
00:00:09,739 --> 00:00:14,910
Woo-jin and Mr. Moon got hurt,
so we're at the ER.

3
00:00:15,578 --> 00:00:17,038
Are they badly hurt?

4
00:00:18,122 --> 00:00:21,083
Woo-jin has a knife wound
on his left hand,

5
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:23,502
and Mr. Moon has a gash on his forehead.

6
00:00:23,586 --> 00:00:24,795
My goodness…

7
00:00:26,047 --> 00:00:27,715
It's all my fault.

8
00:00:28,924 --> 00:00:30,551
It's all because of me.

9
00:00:30,634 --> 00:00:32,011
Oh, Gun-woo…

10
00:00:32,094 --> 00:00:33,971
This is not on you.

11
00:00:35,389 --> 00:00:37,099
These things happen.

12
00:00:37,183 --> 00:00:38,017
MIN GANG-YONG

13
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:40,227
Unexpected things come up.

14
00:00:40,728 --> 00:00:41,645
SIR, GUN-WOO NEEDS HELP

15
00:00:41,729 --> 00:00:46,442
But the most painful moments,
when you're at rock bottom,

16
00:00:47,276 --> 00:00:50,321
can become a turning point for the better.

17
00:00:52,281 --> 00:00:55,034
If I'd just done what they said,

18
00:00:55,951 --> 00:00:57,912
no one would've gotten hurt.

19
00:00:59,413 --> 00:01:01,207
That's all I can think about.

20
00:01:01,957 --> 00:01:05,002
No one wants you getting involved
in that shady deal.

21
00:01:05,503 --> 00:01:07,755
That's why everyone's helping you.

22
00:01:08,589 --> 00:01:11,467
I'd rather get hurt myself, Mom.

23
00:01:12,093 --> 00:01:12,968
Gun-woo.

24
00:01:13,552 --> 00:01:17,098
What would you have done
if Woo-jin said he'd do that?

25
00:01:18,974 --> 00:01:21,560
You would've stopped him no matter what.

26
00:01:23,062 --> 00:01:23,896
See?

27
00:01:23,979 --> 00:01:26,315
That's how everyone else feels now.

28
00:01:26,816 --> 00:01:28,275
So,

29
00:01:29,193 --> 00:01:30,611
let's get through this.

30
00:01:30,694 --> 00:01:34,031
Bad things will pass
if we just hang in there.

31
00:01:35,366 --> 00:01:37,576
Good things will come.

32
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:43,874
Okay.

33
00:01:45,376 --> 00:01:46,418
Son.

34
00:01:47,211 --> 00:01:48,254
Stay strong.

35
00:01:50,089 --> 00:01:50,923
Okay.

36
00:01:52,174 --> 00:01:53,801
This will sting.

37
00:01:54,426 --> 00:01:56,345
Yes, it stings. Hang in there.

38
00:01:56,929 --> 00:01:58,389
I'll numb the area now.

39
00:01:59,265 --> 00:02:01,392
Wait.

40
00:02:01,475 --> 00:02:03,310
-Doctor.
-Yes?

41
00:02:03,394 --> 00:02:06,939
Please make it nice and pretty
so it doesn't scar.

42
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:08,774
Understood, sir.

43
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:20,870
-Just a quick sting.
-Wait!

44
00:02:23,998 --> 00:02:25,207
-Almost done.
-Ouch!

45
00:02:26,375 --> 00:02:27,626
All done.

46
00:02:36,385 --> 00:02:38,762
Sir, how's the pain?

47
00:02:41,015 --> 00:02:43,100
Ma'am, back in the day,

48
00:02:44,393 --> 00:02:48,647
I was stabbed in the stomach twice,
but I made a full recovery.

49
00:02:49,231 --> 00:02:50,566
Oh…

50
00:02:51,066 --> 00:02:54,111
Are you in a gang?

51
00:02:54,195 --> 00:02:55,738
Not at all.

52
00:02:56,947 --> 00:02:58,908
I'm a boxer, ma'am.

53
00:02:58,991 --> 00:03:01,994
I'm not a gangster or anything like that.

54
00:03:02,077 --> 00:03:03,204
-So…
-I see.

55
00:03:03,787 --> 00:03:05,164
Anyway,

56
00:03:06,498 --> 00:03:09,710
it's been a while since I stepped down
from the ring as a pro.

57
00:03:10,711 --> 00:03:13,797
But with this hand injury,
my fighting days are over.

58
00:03:14,298 --> 00:03:15,132
Well…

59
00:03:15,758 --> 00:03:17,676
Sir, you shouldn't fight.

60
00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:21,013
I must fight.

61
00:03:21,096 --> 00:03:23,390
You shouldn't fight with this hand.

62
00:03:23,474 --> 00:03:26,518
Ma'am, I'm Hong Woo-jin.

63
00:03:26,602 --> 00:03:28,103
If I can't fight,

64
00:03:28,687 --> 00:03:31,565
I'll become a nobody.

65
00:03:32,691 --> 00:03:34,193
I'm a boxer.

66
00:03:35,736 --> 00:03:37,738
I'm the invincible Marine Southpaw.

67
00:03:38,447 --> 00:03:39,782
Then you must fight.

68
00:03:41,075 --> 00:03:42,034
Fight.

69
00:03:42,868 --> 00:03:44,954
You can do it, okay?

70
00:03:52,253 --> 00:03:53,754
I have to fight.

71
00:04:00,678 --> 00:04:02,763
Sir, are you okay?

72
00:04:02,846 --> 00:04:05,849
Oh, this is nothing.

73
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:08,811
The doctor stitched me up nice and pretty,

74
00:04:08,894 --> 00:04:11,689
so I won't need plastic surgery.

75
00:04:11,772 --> 00:04:15,109
This is really delicate work.

76
00:04:15,192 --> 00:04:18,696
If you botch it, you have to rip it out
and start from scratch.

77
00:04:19,196 --> 00:04:20,322
-That's a no.
-Right.

78
00:04:20,406 --> 00:04:23,325
My looks are all I've got.

79
00:04:23,909 --> 00:04:25,619
Hold on. Doctor!

80
00:04:26,662 --> 00:04:28,122
Well, goodness.

81
00:04:28,205 --> 00:04:31,750
If you ever need some fast cash,
please contact me anytime.

82
00:04:32,418 --> 00:04:33,377
Oh.

83
00:04:34,211 --> 00:04:35,045
Please.

84
00:04:35,546 --> 00:04:36,964
Take care.

85
00:04:37,715 --> 00:04:38,841
God.

86
00:04:40,259 --> 00:04:42,136
Damn, my head…

87
00:04:42,219 --> 00:04:44,013
You got injured because of me.

88
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,140
I'm very sorry.

89
00:04:48,976 --> 00:04:49,810
Gun-woo.

90
00:04:52,104 --> 00:04:53,731
My God, have you been crying?

91
00:04:55,274 --> 00:04:56,108
Oh.

92
00:04:57,318 --> 00:04:58,736
Look at you.

93
00:05:00,821 --> 00:05:03,115
You have an iron fist…

94
00:05:04,950 --> 00:05:06,535
but a heart of cotton candy.

95
00:05:09,496 --> 00:05:10,414
I'm sorry.

96
00:05:11,665 --> 00:05:13,751
Promise me one thing.

97
00:05:16,003 --> 00:05:18,881
Here. Harden your heart

98
00:05:19,548 --> 00:05:21,508
like cast iron as well.

99
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:26,013
That way, your people stay safe.

100
00:05:29,433 --> 00:05:30,267
Yes, sir.

101
00:05:33,187 --> 00:05:34,646
-Gun-woo.
-Yes.

102
00:05:35,898 --> 00:05:36,732
Hey, Woo-jin.

103
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,568
-Oh.
-Damn.

104
00:05:39,651 --> 00:05:41,862
You haven't had your hand stitched up yet?

105
00:05:41,945 --> 00:05:43,781
They told me to wait an hour.

106
00:05:43,864 --> 00:05:47,034
The wound is so deep
that they're calling in a specialist.

107
00:05:47,117 --> 00:05:48,911
Good to know.

108
00:05:49,953 --> 00:05:51,538
Listen carefully.

109
00:05:52,664 --> 00:05:54,792
Consider skipping the anesthesia.

110
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:57,127
-Stitches without anesthesia?
-Hey!

111
00:05:57,211 --> 00:06:00,172
I've got six injections on my dome.

112
00:06:00,255 --> 00:06:03,967
It hurt so much that I teared up,
but I only got four stitches.

113
00:06:04,051 --> 00:06:06,220
Forget the interest.
I didn't even get my principal back.

114
00:06:06,303 --> 00:06:07,179
GANG-YONG

115
00:06:07,262 --> 00:06:09,098
Sir, I'd need those shots…

116
00:06:09,181 --> 00:06:11,475
You don't. I'm telling you.

117
00:06:11,558 --> 00:06:12,393
But, sir…

118
00:06:12,476 --> 00:06:14,228
Okay, fine.

119
00:06:14,311 --> 00:06:16,688
Do you want a squeeze toy just in case?

120
00:06:18,023 --> 00:06:18,857
Hello, Gang-yong.

121
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:22,403
Hey, champion. Where are you now?

122
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:23,946
Well…

123
00:06:26,073 --> 00:06:28,409
I'm on my way to Min-beom's company.

124
00:06:28,492 --> 00:06:30,953
I don't know what's going on,
but I've got you.

125
00:06:31,036 --> 00:06:32,704
Don't worry, okay?

126
00:06:33,247 --> 00:06:35,040
We can get through this together.

127
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:36,792
You got that?

128
00:06:37,709 --> 00:06:38,627
Yes, Gang-yong.

129
00:07:11,201 --> 00:07:13,203
BLOODHOUNDS 2

130
00:07:20,294 --> 00:07:22,671
Goodness, are you okay?

131
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:25,549
Yes, thank you so much.

132
00:07:26,925 --> 00:07:27,968
We haven't met…

133
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,721
He's a senior marine to Woo-jin and me.

134
00:07:30,804 --> 00:07:33,265
He helped us take out Kim Myeong-gil.

135
00:07:33,348 --> 00:07:34,933
I'm Moon Gwang-mu.

136
00:07:35,017 --> 00:07:37,436
I've heard so much about you.

137
00:07:38,145 --> 00:07:39,062
I'm Hong Min-beom.

138
00:07:39,146 --> 00:07:40,856
What an honor.

139
00:07:40,939 --> 00:07:44,610
I'm Min Gang-yong,
team leader at Seoul Metro Police.

140
00:07:44,693 --> 00:07:46,111
Yes, sir.

141
00:07:48,155 --> 00:07:50,782
-Sir, this is Tae-yeong--
-Of course I know.

142
00:07:50,866 --> 00:07:54,244
I helped move her IKEA desk last year.

143
00:07:54,328 --> 00:07:55,621
You remember me, right?

144
00:07:55,704 --> 00:07:57,039
Of course.

145
00:07:57,122 --> 00:07:58,874
Only Woo-jin was there back then.

146
00:07:58,957 --> 00:07:59,833
I see.

147
00:07:59,917 --> 00:08:01,752
Let's sit and talk.

148
00:08:01,835 --> 00:08:02,836
-Okay.
-Sure.

149
00:08:12,137 --> 00:08:13,805
If you don't mind me asking,

150
00:08:13,889 --> 00:08:15,849
what line of work are you in?

151
00:08:15,933 --> 00:08:19,811
Well, I run a small…

152
00:08:20,312 --> 00:08:23,315
I'm running a small loan company.

153
00:08:23,398 --> 00:08:25,526
I'm basically a small business owner.

154
00:08:32,699 --> 00:08:35,494
I know how you feel.

155
00:08:35,577 --> 00:08:36,662
But as for me,

156
00:08:36,745 --> 00:08:39,581
I learned the trade under Mr. Choi.

157
00:08:39,665 --> 00:08:43,043
I wouldn't do things
that go against my conscience.

158
00:08:45,254 --> 00:08:47,172
-It's Gwang-mu, right?
-Yes.

159
00:08:47,256 --> 00:08:49,258
I appreciate you helping Gun-woo,

160
00:08:50,008 --> 00:08:51,301
but I'm a cop.

161
00:08:51,927 --> 00:08:54,846
If I see you breaking the law,
I have to do my job.

162
00:08:54,930 --> 00:08:55,931
You understand, right?

163
00:08:56,723 --> 00:08:57,808
I sure do.

164
00:09:00,477 --> 00:09:02,563
Who's handling the break-in at your place?

165
00:09:02,646 --> 00:09:04,731
A detective at Incheon Station.

166
00:09:04,815 --> 00:09:06,066
Give me his number.

167
00:09:06,942 --> 00:09:11,363
If this ever happens again,
call me the first thing, okay?

168
00:09:11,446 --> 00:09:12,990
So I can sort it out faster.

169
00:09:14,366 --> 00:09:15,325
Will do.

170
00:09:16,326 --> 00:09:17,286
LEE WOO-JEONG
CLASS 39

171
00:09:23,667 --> 00:09:25,502
Excuse me. This is urgent.

172
00:09:25,586 --> 00:09:26,503
Sure.

173
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:31,967
Hey, Woo-jeong.

174
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:36,430
Sir, you arrested Kang In-beom
in 2021, right?

175
00:09:38,015 --> 00:09:38,932
Yes, why?

176
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,475
So, Gun-woo.

177
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:45,856
I've been looking into safe places
where your mom can stay comfortably.

178
00:09:45,939 --> 00:09:48,609
Unfortunately,
my hotel is still under construction.

179
00:09:49,318 --> 00:09:51,445
My friend runs the Marriott
in Times Square.

180
00:09:52,237 --> 00:09:55,198
I'll have a room
and a security team ready.

181
00:09:55,782 --> 00:09:58,702
Don't worry. I'll take good care of her.

182
00:09:59,244 --> 00:10:01,330
Is it okay to accept all this?

183
00:10:01,830 --> 00:10:04,750
Remember what you said last time
when we almost gave up?

184
00:10:06,084 --> 00:10:07,294
We'll help you.

185
00:10:07,878 --> 00:10:09,838
It's not over until it's over.

186
00:10:12,507 --> 00:10:14,593
You didn't give up.
That's how we're alive.

187
00:10:14,676 --> 00:10:15,802
This is nothing.

188
00:10:17,262 --> 00:10:20,515
I haven't even begun to pay you back.

189
00:10:21,808 --> 00:10:24,436
Anyway, your mother must be very shocked.

190
00:10:25,562 --> 00:10:26,688
Let's protect her.

191
00:10:27,481 --> 00:10:28,357
Yes.

192
00:10:35,113 --> 00:10:36,281
Gun-woo.

193
00:10:37,157 --> 00:10:38,533
This afternoon,

194
00:10:39,368 --> 00:10:40,619
Kang In-beom escaped.

195
00:10:43,997 --> 00:10:46,375
-What?
-The police are looking into it.

196
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:48,377
They are trying to track him down.

197
00:10:49,252 --> 00:10:51,338
But this seems bigger than I thought.

198
00:11:21,034 --> 00:11:23,286
-I told you to bring her.
-I'm sorry.

199
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:24,579
Hey, you fucker.

200
00:11:24,663 --> 00:11:27,708
I burn 300 million won a year
on your salary, you son of a bitch!

201
00:11:29,501 --> 00:11:30,460
I'm sorry, sir.

202
00:11:34,548 --> 00:11:37,342
Should I send your daughter
to an orphanage?

203
00:11:44,266 --> 00:11:45,100
I'm sorry.

204
00:11:47,811 --> 00:11:48,687
Do it right.

205
00:11:49,604 --> 00:11:50,439
Yes, sir.

206
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:55,068
Fucking dumbass.

207
00:12:26,099 --> 00:12:27,100
Kang In-beom.

208
00:12:29,936 --> 00:12:31,271
Must be nice to be out.

209
00:12:37,235 --> 00:12:38,195
So,

210
00:12:39,279 --> 00:12:40,655
made up your mind?

211
00:12:48,079 --> 00:12:49,122
Work with me.

212
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,795
Then you're set for life.

213
00:13:18,276 --> 00:13:20,320
Kang In-beom has a vendetta against us.

214
00:13:20,987 --> 00:13:23,281
Someone that driven is easy to manipulate.

215
00:13:24,115 --> 00:13:25,867
That's why they broke him out--

216
00:13:27,828 --> 00:13:31,873
The bastards want to leash a wild dog
to turn him into a bloodhound.

217
00:13:31,957 --> 00:13:33,416
Here's what worries me.

218
00:13:36,795 --> 00:13:40,131
In this country,
you don't just break out of prison.

219
00:13:40,841 --> 00:13:43,426
From what I heard,
the plan was pretty meticulous.

220
00:13:44,010 --> 00:13:45,262
They're using a pro.

221
00:13:45,762 --> 00:13:49,349
What if Kim Myeong-gil escapes too?

222
00:13:50,308 --> 00:13:51,309
Min-beom.

223
00:13:51,393 --> 00:13:55,188
Kim Myeong-gil is locked up on an island
20 km off the west coast.

224
00:13:55,272 --> 00:13:57,357
No one can break that bastard out.

225
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:58,650
Don't worry.

226
00:14:01,236 --> 00:14:05,282
I told them to ramp up the surveillance
on Kim Myeong-gil and his crew.

227
00:14:05,365 --> 00:14:07,450
Don't you worry about a thing.

228
00:14:10,579 --> 00:14:13,415
Sir, I just remembered something.

229
00:14:13,498 --> 00:14:14,457
What is it?

230
00:14:15,041 --> 00:14:18,753
Back in the Cyber Investigation Division,
I shut down a site on the dark web.

231
00:14:18,837 --> 00:14:23,341
They specialized in contract killings,
but they also handled prison breaks.

232
00:14:23,425 --> 00:14:26,845
These people operate out of the dark web.

233
00:14:26,928 --> 00:14:29,180
And we never caught the site admin.

234
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:38,273
If you don't have any other plans,

235
00:14:38,356 --> 00:14:40,817
should I look for the gangsters
who attacked us?

236
00:14:41,568 --> 00:14:43,194
You'll look for what?

237
00:14:43,278 --> 00:14:46,031
The gangsters who fought Woo-jin and me.

238
00:14:46,698 --> 00:14:47,532
Why?

239
00:14:47,616 --> 00:14:49,492
I'm trying to be helpful.

240
00:14:49,576 --> 00:14:51,828
I know people too.

241
00:14:52,329 --> 00:14:53,830
Look.

242
00:14:53,914 --> 00:14:56,291
I'm going to handle this by the book.

243
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:58,418
Mr. Min.

244
00:14:59,252 --> 00:15:02,380
Not everything I do is illegal.

245
00:15:03,423 --> 00:15:05,216
I'll be the judge of that.

246
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:08,845
Yeah, so just sit tight for now.

247
00:15:11,264 --> 00:15:12,098
Gang-yong.

248
00:15:16,394 --> 00:15:18,146
It's late.

249
00:15:18,229 --> 00:15:21,191
Let's get Gun-woo's mom
to the hotel first.

250
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,693
Sure, let's do that.

251
00:15:30,408 --> 00:15:34,120
For fuck's sake.
Give me the damn money, you prick!

252
00:15:34,204 --> 00:15:36,164
You're asking the wrong person.

253
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,168
Fucking hell.

254
00:15:40,669 --> 00:15:43,755
Hey, man,
I heard those fuckers were pro boxers.

255
00:15:44,255 --> 00:15:46,591
Fuck, you should've told me that!

256
00:15:46,675 --> 00:15:47,884
Hey.

257
00:15:48,468 --> 00:15:50,095
Calm down, will you?

258
00:15:50,178 --> 00:15:52,055
Calm down, my ass.

259
00:15:52,555 --> 00:15:53,390
Whatever.

260
00:15:54,349 --> 00:15:55,600
Do you see this?

261
00:15:56,101 --> 00:15:58,812
I need stitches for this gash
so it doesn't scar.

262
00:15:58,895 --> 00:16:00,355
So hand over the money.

263
00:16:03,108 --> 00:16:05,360
Let's talk outside, just us.

264
00:16:05,443 --> 00:16:08,154
Quit fucking playing
and cough it up, asshole.

265
00:16:19,249 --> 00:16:20,583
Fuck!

266
00:16:21,918 --> 00:16:23,378
Get off me, you fucker!

267
00:16:27,507 --> 00:16:29,384
I'm sorry!

268
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:31,678
I'm very sorry, sir!

269
00:16:39,769 --> 00:16:41,229
Please stop.

270
00:16:46,568 --> 00:16:47,402
Bite it.

271
